#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:20
msgid ""
"The CUDA toolchain does not expose an exception mechanism today (the "
"hardware could support it, but nvcc/ptxas do not wire it up). A trap "
"instruction kills the kernel and poisons the CUDA context -- subsequent "
"operations on the same context will fail until you handle or recreate it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:25
msgid "`gpu_printf!` -- printing from the GPU"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:27
msgid ""
"`gpu_printf!` lets you print values from device code for quick debugging. It "
"uses CUDA's built-in `vprintf` mechanism:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:30
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{kernel, thread, gpu_printf, DisjointSlice};\n"
"\n"
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn debug_kernel(data: &[f32], mut out: DisjointSlice<f32>) {\n"
"    let idx = thread::index_1d();\n"
"    if idx.get() < 4 {\n"
"        gpu_printf!(\"Thread {} sees value {}\\n\", idx.get(), data[idx."
"get()]);\n"
"    }\n"
"    if let Some(out_elem) = out.get_mut(idx) {\n"
"        *out_elem = data[idx.get()] * 2.0;\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:45
msgid "Important details"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:47
msgid ""
"**Flush requires sync.** Output is buffered on the GPU and only appears on "
"the host after a stream or device synchronization (e.g., `to_host_vec` or "
"`ctx.synchronize()`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:50
msgid ""
"**Buffer size.** The default printf buffer is 1 MiB. If many threads print, "
"output may be truncated. Enlarge with "
"`cudaDeviceSetLimit(cudaLimitPrintfFifoSize, size)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:53
msgid ""
"**Thread ordering.** Output from different threads appears in arbitrary "
"order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:54
msgid ""
"**Performance.** Printf serializes across threads -- avoid it in hot paths. "
"Use it for debugging, not logging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:56
msgid ""
"**Format conversion.** The macro converts Rust `{}` format specifiers to C "
"printf equivalents (`%d`, `%f`, etc.) at compile time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:59
msgid "Why not `println!` or `Debug`?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:61
msgid ""
"Standard Rust formatting (`fmt::Display`, `fmt::Debug`, `format!`, `println!"
"`) requires dynamic dispatch, string allocation, and I/O -- none of which "
"exist on the GPU. `gpu_printf!` bypasses all of this by lowering directly to "
"a CUDA `vprintf` call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:66
msgid "`gpu_assert!` and `trap()`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:68
msgid ""
"For fatal error checking on the device, use `gpu_assert!` or `debug::trap()`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:70
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{kernel, thread, debug, gpu_assert, DisjointSlice};\n"
"\n"
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn checked_kernel(data: &[f32], len: u32, mut out: DisjointSlice<f32>) "
"{\n"
"    let idx = thread::index_1d();\n"
"    gpu_assert!(idx.get() < len as usize);   // traps if false\n"
"\n"
"    if let Some(out_elem) = out.get_mut(idx) {\n"
"        *out_elem = data[idx.get()];\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

