#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:90
msgid "The trap-and-check pattern"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:92
msgid "A common workflow for catching device-side errors:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:94
msgid ""
"// Launch kernel\n"
"// SAFETY: config matches vecadd's 1D indexing and all buffer bounds.\n"
"unsafe { module.vecadd(&stream, config, &a, &b, &mut c) }\n"
"    .expect(\"Launch failed\");\n"
"\n"
"// Synchronize and check for traps\n"
"stream.synchronize().expect(\"Kernel trapped -- check gpu_assert! "
"conditions\");\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:104
msgid ""
"If a `gpu_assert!` fires, synchronization returns an error. The error "
"message doesn't tell you *which* assertion failed, so use `gpu_printf!` "
"alongside assertions to narrow down the problem."
msgstr ""

