#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:198
msgid ""
"If you stop too early, such as at kernel launch or at the first helper call, "
"the variable may honestly print as `<optimized out>` because it has not been "
"loaded into a register yet. For variable checks, prefer a source line after "
"the value is used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:203
msgid ""
"break src/main.rs:412\n"
"run\n"
"info args\n"
"info locals\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:210
msgid ""
"Seeing one variable as `<optimized out>` is not automatically a compiler "
"bug; it can mean \"this value has no live machine location at this exact PC."
"\" Debug info is a map, not a time machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:214
msgid ""
"For inlined helper calls, cuda-oxide also keeps the original owner of each "
"argument. That matters because two different functions can both have an "
"argument numbered `1`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:218
msgid ""
"kernel(data) calls helper(self)\n"
"\n"
"data -> arg #1 in kernel's debug scope\n"
"self -> arg #1 in helper's debug scope, with \"inlined at\" the kernel "
"callsite\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:225
msgid ""
"Without that scope split, LLVM treats the metadata as contradictory and "
"drops it. Debug info is fussy like that; it wants the family tree, not just "
"the surname."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:229
msgid ""
"Use line tables first. They are enough for most \"where did execution go?\" "
"questions, and they avoid the slower CUDA debug target mode. Use full debug "
"when you specifically want `print idx`, `print ptr`, or similar local-"
"variable inspection. Debuggers are allowed to be nosy; they are not always "
"allowed to be fast."
msgstr ""

