#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:251
msgid "Why full debug turns optimization off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:253
msgid ""
"Reliable local inspection and aggressive optimization pull in opposite "
"directions. An optimized value usually lives in a register only across the "
"short window where it is used; outside that window the debugger honestly has "
"nowhere to read it from, so `info locals` shows `<optimized out>`. The only "
"way to make a variable inspectable for its whole scope is to keep it in "
"**memory** and describe it with `llvm.dbg.declare`, the way every debug "
"build does (`gcc -O0`, `rustc` debug, and nvcc `-G`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:261
msgid "So `CUDA_OXIDE_DEBUG=full` is a `-G`-style build. It automatically:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:263
msgid "keeps every source local in its stack slot (skips Pliron `mem2reg`),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:264
msgid "skips annotated loop unrolling, which requires `mem2reg`'s SSA form,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:265
msgid "skips LLVM `opt -O2`, and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:266
msgid "runs `llc` at `-O0`,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:268
msgid ""
"so the locals you see in cuda-gdb are real and stable. You do not need to "
"set `CUDA_OXIDE_NO_OPT=1` yourself; full mode implies it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:0
msgid "Setting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:0
msgid "`CUDA_OXIDE_DEBUG=off`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/error-handling-and-debugging.md:0
